info.description: Race through a map of hazardous terrain types, pushing rival rodents out of the way and terraforming different areas to your advantage!
info.helpText:
Note on Fox variant:

* 6 bonus fox tiles are included with the following rules:

* If the appropriate terrain bonus tile is still available, then it must be used. If it's not available, use your choice of a generic tile (if still available) or a fox tile (if still available). If neither is available, then you don't get a bonus tile.

* The cost of moving onto a fox tile is one movement point (like a generic tile). However, when you move onto it you must discard 3 cards. If you don't have 3 cards in hand, you cannot move onto a fox tile on your turn. However, you can still get pushed onto a fox tile on another player's turn, even if you have less than 3 cards in hand, and in that case you must discard up to 3 cards.

fields.text: By default, you will play the base map with 2 tokens per player. But you may select different options below.
